Arsenal on Thursday night defeated Wolves 2-1 to rekindle hope of making the top in the English Premier League of the current season.
The Thursday victory at the Emirates Stadium placed Arsenal in fifth position, one point behind Manchester United who are on the fourth position on the EPL table. Arsenal have two matches to play, and one of the matches is against Chelsea.
They are optimistic to sail into the top four and qualify for the European Champions League next season.
